						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Fragment built into the village-gate.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṅghaṇa—A.D. 1226-27.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1148, [Vyaya], ba. Amāvāsyā, Monday, Saṁkramaṇa.</hi> The names of the month and the saṁkramaṇa are lost. The year given corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1226-27.</hi></p>						

						<p>Only a part of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of a subordinate (name lost) of the king is preserved in this inscription. </p>						

						</summary>
